{"title":"Fire pillar","url":"https://nethackwiki.com/wiki/Fire_pillar","type":"markdown","data":"**Fire pillar** is a [monster spell](/wiki/Monster_spell \"Monster spell\") that appears in *[NetHack](/wiki/NetHack \"NetHack\")*, and is used by high-level [clerical spellcasters](/wiki/Clerical_spell \"Clerical spell\").\n\n[ ]\n\n## Contents\n\n- [1 Description](#Description)\n\n- [2 Messages](#Messages)\n\n- [3 Variants](#Variants)\n\n  - [3.1 dNethack](#dNethack)\n  - [3.2 EvilHack](#EvilHack)\n\n- [4 References](#References)\n\n## Description\n\nFire pillar can be used by any monster that can cast clerical spells and is at least [level](/wiki/Monster_level \"Monster level\") 13.[\\[1\\]](#cite_note-1)[\\[2\\]](#cite_note-2) When cast, a pillar of [fire](/wiki/Fire \"Fire\") strikes the [player](/wiki/Player \"Player\") character's square - the pillar deals 8d6 fire damage and burns flammable armor, weapons and other items on that square, as well as in your inventory if you are hit, and additionally cures [sliming](/wiki/Sliming \"Sliming\").[\\[3\\]](#cite_note-3) [Half spell damage](/wiki/Half_spell_damage \"Half spell damage\") cuts the damage to half, rounded up, while [fire resistance](/wiki/Fire_resistance \"Fire resistance\") nullifies the damage entirely.[\\[4\\]](#cite_note-4)[\\[5\\]](#cite_note-5)\n\n*The following information pertains to an upcoming version ([3.7.0](/wiki/3.7.0 \"3.7.0\")). If this version is now released, please verify that it is still accurate, then update the page to incorporate this information.*\n\nAs of [commit 6b8079a1](https://github.com/NetHack/NetHack/commit/6b8079a16f425aa80239b0b1009ec98a70af56ff), the spell also melts [ice](/wiki/Ice \"Ice\") on the target square.\n\n## Messages\n\n- A pillar of fire strikes all around you!\n\n  A monster caster the fire pillar spell at you.[\\[6\\]](#cite_note-6)\n\n## Variants\n\n### dNethack\n\nIn [dNetHack](/wiki/DNetHack \"DNetHack\"), various monsters besides clerical casters can use this spell.\n\nThe [Stranger](/wiki/Stranger \"Stranger\") can cast fire pillar through another monster as part of the yellow smiting caused by his \"intervention\".\n\n### EvilHack\n\nIn [EvilHack](/wiki/EvilHack \"EvilHack\"), monsters can use the flame pillar spell against other monsters.\n\n[Kathryn the Ice Queen](/wiki/Kathryn_the_Ice_Queen \"Kathryn the Ice Queen\") and [Asmodeus](/wiki/Asmodeus \"Asmodeus\") will never use this spell, casting [lightning](/wiki/Lightning \"Lightning\") instead. Tame monsters, peaceful monsters and [major demons](/wiki/Major_demon \"Major demon\") will cast fire pillar in lieu of [summon minion](/wiki/Summon_minion \"Summon minion\").\n\n## References\n\n1. [↑](#cite_ref-1) [src/mcastu.c in NetHack 3.6.7, line 34](https://github.com/NetHack/NetHack/blob/NetHack-3.6.7_Released/src/mcastu.c#L34)\n2. [↑](#cite_ref-2) [src/mcastu.c in NetHack 3.6.7, line 153](https://github.com/NetHack/NetHack/blob/NetHack-3.6.7_Released/src/mcastu.c#L153)\n3. [↑](#cite_ref-3) [src/mcastu.c in NetHack 3.6.7, line 544](https://github.com/NetHack/NetHack/blob/NetHack-3.6.7_Released/src/mcastu.c#L544)\n4. [↑](#cite_ref-4) [src/mcastu.c in NetHack 3.6.7, line 551](https://github.com/NetHack/NetHack/blob/NetHack-3.6.7_Released/src/mcastu.c#L551)\n5. [↑](#cite_ref-5) [src/mcastu.c in NetHack 3.6.7, line 546](https://github.com/NetHack/NetHack/blob/NetHack-3.6.7_Released/src/mcastu.c#L546)\n6. [↑](#cite_ref-6) [src/mcastu.c in NetHack 3.6.7, line 545](https://github.com/NetHack/NetHack/blob/NetHack-3.6.7_Released/src/mcastu.c#L545)\n\n[![This article has been updated to reflect NetHack 3.6.7. Click here for more information.](/images/f/f7/Nh367-icon.png)](/wiki/NetHackWiki:Next_version \"This article has been updated to reflect NetHack 3.6.7. Click here for more information.\")\n","html":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html class=\"client-nojs\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\"/>\n<title>Fire pillar - NetHack Wiki</title>\n<script>document.do